author: Paramount Plus
description:
The story of the murder spree, manhunt and capture from the perspective of a Lincolnite in 1958, immersed in fear and horror. Information unfolds across the news, which depicts Charles and Caril as teenage lovers on the run, and public opinion is shaped against Caril. She is made to seem not just as guilty as Charles, but perhaps the mastermind of the whole event. The archival crime spree story is intercut with present day interviews with those close to the case. There is much more to this story than people think. SHOWTIME® Original Series premiere.

Stream The 12th Victim on the Paramount+ Premium Plan.

author: Paramount Plus
description:
"Chapter One - A Body in a Canal" - Based on a best-selling book, this SHOWTIME® Original five-part true crime docuseries investigates the unsolved murders of eight women whose bodies were discovered in drainage canals and on desolate back roads in and around Jennings, Louisiana. Examining the lives of the young victims, this series uncovers secrets of the troubled town and leads to shocking accusations by the relatives and friends of victims of corruption and institutional injustices.

description:
"Deus Light" - Grant Amato enjoys a life of success and privilege before his obsession with a Bulgarian cam model lands him in the center of a murder investigation. CTRL+ALT+DESIRE takes viewers inside the close relationship between director Colin Archdeacon and Grant Aamto to uncover shocking new details about the case. As Grant's narrative unravels, the series transforms into a gripping profile of obsession, loneliness and family turmoil.
